.TH SUTURE "1" "April 2026" "Suture v5.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
suture \- Universal Semantic Version Control System
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B suture
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIcommand\fR [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Suture is a universal semantic version control system that supports
video (OTIO), document (DOCX/XLSX/PPTX), and data (CSV/JSON/XML/YAML)
workflows with content-aware semantic diffing, merging, and integrity
verification.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Initialize a new Suture repository
.TP
.B status
Show repository status
.TP
.B ignore
Inspect .sutureignore patterns
.TP
.B add
Add files to the staging area
.TP
.B rm
Remove files from the working tree and staging area
.TP
.B commit
Create a commit
.TP
.B branch
Branch operations
.TP
.B log
Show commit history
.TP
.B checkout
Switch to a different branch
.TP
.B switch
Switch to a different branch (modern alternative to checkout)
.TP
.B restore
Restore working tree files
.TP
.B mv
Move or rename a tracked file
.TP
.B diff
Show differences between commits or branches
.TP
.B revert
Revert a commit
.TP
.B merge
Merge a branch into the current branch
.TP
.B merge\-file
Perform three\-way file merge
.TP
.B apply
Apply a patch/diff file to the working tree
.TP
.B cherry\-pick
Apply a specific commit onto the current branch
.TP
.B rebase
Rebase the current branch onto another branch
.TP
.B blame
Show per\-line commit attribution for a file
.TP
.B tag
Tag operations
.TP
.B config
Get or set configuration values
.TP
.B remote
Remote operations
.TP
.B push
Push patches to a remote Hub
.TP
.B pull
Pull patches from a remote Hub
.TP
.B fetch
Fetch patches from a remote Hub without merging
.TP
.B ls\-remote
List references on a remote Hub
.TP
.B clone
Clone a repository from a remote Hub
.TP
.B reset
Reset HEAD to a specific commit
.TP
.B key
Signing key management
.TP
.B stash
Stash management
.TP
.B completions
Generate shell completions
.TP
.B show
Show detailed information about a commit
.TP
.B reflog
Show the reference log (HEAD movements)
.TP
.B drivers
List available semantic drivers
.TP
.B shortlog
Show compact commit summary grouped by author
.TP
.B notes
Manage commit notes
.TP
.B worktree
Manage working trees
.TP
.B version
Show version information
.TP
.B verify
Verify commit signatures
.TP
.B gc
Garbage collect unreachable objects
.TP
.B grep
Search for a pattern in tracked files
.TP
.B fsck
Verify repository integrity
.TP
.B doctor
Check repository health and configuration
.TP
.B audit
Inspect the tamper\-evident audit log
.TP
.B clean
Remove untracked files from the working tree
.TP
.B describe
Describe a commit using the nearest tag
.TP
.B rev\-parse
Parse revision names to hashes
.TP
.B git
Interact with Git repositories
.TP
.B bisect
Binary search for bug\-introducing commit
.TP
.B hook
Manage repository hooks
.TP
.B classification
Bulk classification marking scanning and compliance reporting
.TP
.B undo
Undo the last operation
.TP
.B squash
Squash N commits into one
.TP
.B sync
Synchronize with remote
.TP
.B tui
Launch terminal UI
.TP
.B export
Export a clean snapshot without repository metadata
.TP
.B report
Generate reports about the repository
.TP
.B batch
Batch operations for managing multiple files or clients
.TP
.B timeline
OTIO timeline operations
.TP
.B archive
Create an archive of the repository
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-C " " \fI<REPO_PATH>\fR
Run as if suture was started in <path>.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR suture-init (1),
.BR suture-add (1),
.BR suture-commit (1),
.BR suture-log (1),
.BR suture-diff (1)
